---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { categories, entryCount } from '../data';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---
<Layout title="Monitoring Frontier AI" description="A taxonomy, bibliography, and frank assessment of runtime monitoring for frontier AI models.">
  <h1>Monitoring Frontier AI</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Using smaller or weaker models — and small probes trained on internal
    activations — to flag misbehavior in larger frontier models at runtime
    has become the central operational bet of frontier-lab safety programs.
    This review maps the subfield.
  </p>

  <p>
    The empirical base is narrower than the rhetoric implies. The field has
    cohered around four approach families — behavioral monitors, activation
    probes, protocol-level AI control, and training-signal uses — each with
    genuine progress and each with load-bearing assumptions that are
    contested. Korbak et al.'s "fragile opportunity" framing (2025) treats
    chain-of-thought monitorability as a contingent, protectable property,
    while Baker et al. (2025) show that optimization against monitors
    actively destroys that property. No paper yet shows how to square that
    circle.
  </p>

  <p>
    This review covers what the field looks like as of April 2026. The
    bibliography entries below are annotated with the source report's prose
    verbatim; the <a href={`${base}/critical-assessment/`}>critical
    assessment</a> is where the review earns its keep — it catalogues which
    of the field's load-bearing results are under-replicated, which probe
    AUROCs should be read skeptically, and where the community's apparent
    consensus is narrower than it appears.
  </p>

  <p>
    Browse the taxonomy by jumping to any branch. Each category page lists
    the canonical papers inline with annotations and links.
  </p>

  <a class="critical-link" href={`${base}/critical-assessment/`}>
    <strong>→ Read the critical assessment</strong><br />
    <span style="color:var(--fg-muted); font-size:0.92rem;">Blind spots, failed replications, hype vs. evidence — the report's frank read on the field.</span>
  </a>

  <h2>The taxonomy</h2>
  <div class="taxonomy-grid">
    {categories.map((c) => (
      <a class="tax-card" href={`${base}/taxonomy/${c.id}/`}>
        <h3>{c.name}</h3>
        <p class="short">{c.short}</p>
        <span class="count">{entryCount(c.id)} entries</span>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <p style="margin-top:2rem; color:var(--fg-muted); font-size:0.92rem;">
    This is a single-curator AI-assisted compilation. See the
    <a href={`${base}/about/`}>about page</a> for provenance, scope, and
    maintenance policy.
  </p>
</Layout>
